# Vocal project conventions

Package namespace: `org.openaac.vocal`.

## Architecture

- Multi-module: `app`, `core/domain`, `core/data`, `core/ui`, `feature/*`
- MVVM in feature modules; business logic in use cases under `core/domain`
- Repository interfaces in domain; implementations in `core/data`
- Use Hilt for dependency injection

## Offline-first (v1)

- No network calls unless explicitly requested for a cloud feature
- Persist structured data in Room; preferences in DataStore
- Store custom icons and recorded audio as local files with paths in Room

## Strings and i18n

- Never hardcode user-visible text in Composables or ViewModels
- Use `strings.xml` in the owning module
- English first; design for future locales

## Code style

- Prefer small, reviewable changes
- Match existing naming and file layout
- Use Kotlin coroutines and Flow for async data

## Open source

- Apache 2.0 license
- Document public APIs and non-obvious AAC behavior
